Certainly! Below is a simple web app created in HTML that encapsulates a game concept where you play as a character who is dead. The game involves navigating through simple choices to find peace. The implementation includes embedded CSS for styling and JavaScript for game logic.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Dead Man's Choices</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #222;
            color: #f0f0f0;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 50px;
        }
        .game-container {
            background-color: #333;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
            margin: auto;
            width: 300px;
        }
        button {
            background-color: #555;
            color: #fff;
            border: none;
            padding: 10px 15px;
            margin: 10px;
            border-radius: 5px;
            cursor: pointer;
        }
        button:hover {
            background-color: #777;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="game-container">
    <h1>Dead Man's Choices</h1>
    <p id="description">You find yourself in a dark void. Choose your path.</p>
    <div id="choices"></div>
</div>

<script>
    const game = {
        state: "start",
        choices: {
            start: {
                description: "You are dead. You can either move towards the light or wander into the darkness.",
                options: [
                    { text: "Towards the light", next: "light" },
                    { text: "Wander into darkness", next: "darkness" }
                ]
            },
            light: {
                description: "You feel warmth. You see a figure. Do you approach?",
                options: [
                    { text: "Yes, approach the figure", next: "figure" },
                    { text: "No, stay back", next: "stay" }
                ]
            },
            darkness: {
                description: "You feel lost. Shadows surround you. Do you call out?",
                options: [
                    { text: "Yes, call out", next: "echo" },
                    { text: "No, keep walking", next: "lost" }
                ]
            },
            figure: {
                description: "It was a loved one. They welcome you. You find peace. Game Over.",
                options: []
            },
            stay: {
                description: "You drift away, lost forever. Game Over.",
                options: []
            },
            echo: {
                description: "Your voice echoes back, but no one comes. You fade away. Game Over.",
                options: []
            },
            lost: {
                description: "You stumble endlessly in darkness. Game Over.",
                options: []
            }
        },
        start() {
            this.displayChoices(this.state);
        },
        displayChoices(state) {
            const choiceContainer = document.getElementById('choices');
            choiceContainer.innerHTML = '';

            const current = this.choices[state];
            document.getElementById('description').innerText = current.description;

            current.options.forEach(option => {
                const button = document.createElement('button');
                button.innerText = option.text;
                button.onclick = () => this.displayChoices(option.next);
                choiceContainer.appendChild(button);
            });

            if (current.options.length === 0) {
                const button = document.createElement('button');
                button.innerText = "Restart";
                button.onclick = () => this.restart();
                choiceContainer.appendChild(button);
            }
        },
        restart() {
            this.state = "start";
            this.start();
        }
    };

    game.start();
</script>

</body>
</html>
```

### How to Use

1. Copy the above code into a text file.
2. Save the file with a `.html` extension (e.g., `dead_mans_choices.html`).
3. Open the file in a web browser.

### Game Concept
- The game is a text-based adventure where the player makes choices about the next steps they want to take after dying. 
- The choices lead to different endings, either finding peace or losing oneself. 
- At the end of any scenario, the player can restart the game.

Feel free to modify and expand on the gameâ€™s choices and consequences! Enjoy!

Certainly! Below is an HTML web app that contains an interactive section about bean beetles, along with embedded CSS and JavaScript. The app provides information on bean beetles and allows users to explore various facts about them.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Bean Beetles Info</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #e0f7fa;
            color: #005b5c;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 20px;
        }
        .info-container {
            background-color: #ffffff;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
            max-width: 600px;
            margin: auto;
        }
        button {
            background-color: #00796b;
            color: #ffffff;
            border: none;
            padding: 10px 15px;
            margin: 10px;
            border-radius: 5px;
            cursor: pointer;
        }
        button:hover {
            background-color: #004d40;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="info-container">
    <h1>Welcome to the Bean Beetles Info Hub!</h1>
    <p id="content">Click the button below to learn interesting facts about bean beetles!</p>
    <button id="learnMore">Learn More</button>
    <div id="facts" style="margin-top: 20px;"></div>
</div>

<script>
    const facts = [
        "Bean beetles are small insects belonging to the family Chrysomelidae.",
        "They primarily feed on the seeds of legumes, which is why they are often found in areas with bean plants.",
        "The scientific name for the common bean beetle is Callosobruchus maculatus.",
        "Bean beetles are known for their distinctively spotted appearance, which can vary in color and pattern.",
        "They are used in biology classrooms and laboratories to study genetic traits due to their quick life cycle and ease of breeding.",
        "Adult bean beetles emerge from infested seeds to mate and lay eggs on new seeds, continuing the lifecycle.",
        "They are considered agricultural pests as they can cause significant damage to stored legumes and grains.",
        "Despite their status as pests, bean beetles are also interesting subjects for research in evolution and population genetics."
    ];

    document.getElementById("learnMore").addEventListener("click", function() {
        const factsContainer = document.getElementById("facts");
        factsContainer.innerHTML = ''; // Clear existing facts

        facts.forEach((fact, index) => {
            const factElement = document.createElement("p");
            factElement.textContent = `${index + 1}. ${fact}`;
            factsContainer.appendChild(factElement);
        });
    });
</script>

</body>
</html>
```

### How to Use

1. Copy the above code into a text file.
2. Save the file with a `.html` extension (e.g., `bean_beetles_info.html`).
3. Open the file in a web browser.

### Overview of the Web App
- The web app has a welcoming interface and a button that, when clicked, reveals interesting facts about bean beetles.
- Facts include their biology, behavior, and significance in agricultural studies.
- The design is responsive and visually appealing, suitable for educational purposes.

Feel free to modify or expand the facts as necessary! Enjoy learning about bean beetles!
